<TEXT>
   <s><ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Waxman Industries Inc.</ENAMEX> <EVENT eid="e1" class="REPORTING" >said</EVENT> holders of <NUMEX TYPE="MONEY">$6,542,000</NUMEX> face amount of its <CARDINAL>6</CARDINAL> <NUMEX TYPE="PERCENT">1/4%</NUMEX> convertible subordinated debentures, <EVENT eid="e11" class="STATE" >due</EVENT> <TIMEX3 tid="t13" type="DATE" temporalFunction="false" functionInDocument="NONE" value="2007-03-15" >March 15, 2007</TIMEX3>, have <EVENT eid="e2" class="I_ACTION" >elected</EVENT> <SIGNAL sid="s3" >to</SIGNAL> <EVENT eid="e4" class="OCCURRENCE" >convert</EVENT> the debt into <CARDINAL>about 683,000</CARDINAL> common shares.</s> 

   <s>The conversion price is <NUMEX TYPE="MONEY">$9.58</NUMEX> a share.</s> 

   <s>The company <EVENT eid="e6" class="REPORTING" >said</EVENT> the holders <EVENT eid="e7" class="STATE" >represent</EVENT> <NUMEX TYPE="PERCENT">52%</NUMEX> of the face amount of the debentures.</s> 

   <s><ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Waxman</ENAMEX> sells a variety of hardware products for the home repair market.</s> 

</TEXT>

